<!-- ── SECTION 1: SUPPORTING DOCUMENTATION ───────────── -->
<section class="doc-section" id="supporting-docs">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="doc-section-inner">
      <div class="doc-section-header">
        <div class="doc-section-num">01</div>
        <div class="doc-section-titles">
          <div class="doc-section-eyebrow">Section One</div>
          <h2 class="doc-section-title">Additional Supporting Documentation</h2>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-body">
        <p>
          The <strong>"Other" opt-in method</strong> refers to consent collected directly by
          participating transit agency staff during passenger registration, intake, ride
          scheduling, or updates to passenger communication preferences.
        </p>
        <p>
          Agency staff inform passengers that SMS messages are used <em>only for operational
          transportation communications</em>, including ride confirmations, pickup reminders,
          schedule changes, cancellations, and dispatch-related updates. The passenger's
          mobile number and SMS consent preference are recorded in TransitAssistant.
        </p>
        <p>
          SMS messages are <strong>not used for third-party marketing or unrelated promotional
          campaigns</strong>. Passengers may opt out at any time by replying STOP and may
          request assistance by replying HELP.
        </p>

        <div class="doc-callout">
          <div class="doc-callout-label">Opt-out &amp; assistance keywords</div>
          <p>Passengers may control their SMS subscription at any time using these standard keywords:</p>
          <div class="keyword-row">
            <span class="doc-keyword">STOP</span>
            <span class="doc-keyword">HELP</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>
          Message frequency varies based on ride activity and service changes.
          <em>Message and data rates may apply.</em>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── SECTION 2: PRIVACY POLICY ─────────────────────── -->
<section class="doc-section" id="privacy-policy">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="doc-section-inner">
      <div class="doc-section-header">
        <div class="doc-section-num">02</div>
        <div class="doc-section-titles">
          <div class="doc-section-eyebrow">Section Two</div>
          <h2 class="doc-section-title">SMS Privacy Policy</h2>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-body">
        <p>
          <strong>SRR LLC</strong> operates TransitAssistant, a software platform used by
          participating transit agencies to support passenger transportation services.
        </p>
        <p>
          When a passenger provides a mobile phone number and consents to receive SMS
          notifications, the phone number may be used to send operational transportation-related
          text messages. These messages may include:
        </p>

        <ul class="doc-list">
          <li>Ride confirmations</li>
          <li>Pickup reminders</li>
          <li>Schedule changes</li>
          <li>Cancellations</li>
          <li>Dispatch updates</li>
          <li>Other service-related notifications</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          <strong>SRR LLC and participating transit agencies do not sell, rent, or share
          mobile phone numbers with third parties for marketing purposes.</strong>
          Mobile phone numbers are used only to support transportation service communications
          and related system operations.
        </p>
        <p>
          SMS message data may be processed by communication service providers and wireless
          carriers as necessary to deliver text messages. <em>Message and data rates may apply.</em>
        </p>
        <p>
          Passengers may opt out of SMS messages at any time by replying STOP. Passengers may
          request assistance by replying HELP or by contacting their participating transit agency.
        </p>

        <div class="doc-callout">
          <div class="doc-callout-label">Questions &amp; contact</div>
          <p>
            For questions about SMS communications or this privacy policy, passengers should
            contact the participating transit agency providing the transportation service.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── SECTION 3: TERMS AND CONDITIONS ───────────────── -->
<section class="doc-section" id="terms-conditions">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="doc-section-inner">
      <div class="doc-section-header">
        <div class="doc-section-num">03</div>
        <div class="doc-section-titles">
          <div class="doc-section-eyebrow">Section Three</div>
          <h2 class="doc-section-title">SMS Terms and Conditions</h2>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-body">
        <p>
          By providing a mobile phone number and consenting to receive SMS notifications,
          the passenger agrees to receive text messages from the participating transit agency
          through <strong>TransitAssistant</strong>, operated by <strong>SRR LLC</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          SMS messages are used for operational transportation communications, including
          ride confirmations, pickup reminders, schedule changes, cancellations, dispatch
          updates, and other service-related notifications.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Message frequency</strong> varies based on ride activity, scheduled trips,
          cancellations, service changes, and agency communications.
          <em>Message and data rates may apply.</em>
        </p>

        <div class="doc-callout">
          <div class="doc-callout-label">Opt-out &amp; help keywords</div>
          <p>
            Passengers may opt out at any time by replying <strong>STOP</strong>. After replying
            STOP, the passenger may receive a confirmation message and will no longer receive
            SMS notifications unless they opt in again.
          </p>
